1. Use Sublime Text and I-Term to code. 
2. Create 'web server' folder on desktop to store 3 files (style.css, index.html and script.js)
3. Type 'html' on index.html file and press tab key to have the file filled with html base code.

4. index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>My website</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style.css">       # tag css files 
</head>
<body>
	<h1>I am learning how to build my own website!</h1>            # java script code in body 
</body>
</html>

5. style.css

body{
	background-color: yellow
}

6. script.js

use 'console log' --- like print in python --- result show in console not browser
